readability_reflection: I think concatenation is easier to read in smaller scales but in bigger scales interpolation is better. One of the concatenation examples had a bunch of parenthesis and the quotation marks were hard to determine what they were around, something like "(a " + " b) " ...
comprehension_debugging: Concatenation was easier to understand I think for the outcomes of what was going to happen but that's because I'm inexperienced with interpolation.
preference_rationale: Probably interpolation if I got used to it more, I've never used it before so I probably got some questions wrong but if I knew what they did I feel like it would be easier.
learning_curve: I've always used concatenation so it was easier to understand the outcome of what was given compared to interpolation. Actually reading it was just as hard if not harder though.
